caption: Best place to go in Lafayette! The service is amazing and the food and drink are as well! Highly recommend for a night in town or a special occasion!

We were in Lafayette for the weekend and Pamplona came highly recommended. Pamplona did not disappoint. We stuck with small plates: hummus, seared scallops, Mac and Gouda, duck confit, crawfish croquettes, and the piece de resistance - flan. It exceeded expectations. Pamplona has an EXTENSIVE cocktail menu - try it. Great atmosphere. Excellent service.
Good service by Ale 🍺
Always unique great food and drinks. Unique dun atmosphere
Pamplona never disappoints.

No words - well a couple BEST IN TOWN!!! Oh pamplona how I miss you - nothing in town compares to your perfection - we have been many times and love the consistency and perfection you offer - hopefully we can meet at the bar very soon-
Christmas decorations amazing, definitely put me in the spirit.
Absolutely superb 👌  Can't wait until the next time 😀
Such a cool place.  The service and food are amazing.  The ambiance is so festive.  Love all the costumes.
Great service. Lovely food and drink. A favorite place in a town full of good food. Duck fat fries. Bread. Tapas of all kinds. Wines and excellent cocktails.
The Miracle Christmas and Pop-up Halloween are yearly favorites!
Great food, better service. Thanks Emily!
Delicious food great service

Best dining experience in years! I just happened to be in Lafayette traveling through. Food looked good so decided to arrive at opening at 5. There was a line! I sat at bar. Theme that night was Little Shop of Horrors so all servers were dressed in costume mostly drag! Service was spot on. I had a fantastic house salad and the spicy meatballs.
Always fantastic food, strong drinks, and great atmosphere.
Delicious food and awesome atmosphere
Terrible drinks
Festive atmosphere, great service, the food was good and the cocktails are even better.

One of my favorites!  We dined at Pamplona last weekend for my nieces birthday.  The drinks were amazing. The wine was delightful.  The waitstaff was very attentive.  Every plate we tried (and I think we tried most of them!) was better than the one before.   Our son is coming for a visit soon and we will probably... no we WILL...be returning for another fun evening.

One of my favorite restaurants to visit in Lafayette! If you can get a table outside on a cool night, it's one of the most romantic spots to take your love! Waitstaff is always helpful and courteous. The drinks are well-made and the food is always delicious. The bacon-wrapped dates are incredible!!!
Great spirits, good appetizers but my  entree was to salty.

Absolutely fantastic assortment of food and drinks. We went for my wife's birthday and they were able to accommodate our numbers and the food was to die for! Would come back and will always recommend!
Really good vegan options. We enjoyed the vegan paella, blistered shishitos, and fries without the duck fat.

The scallop small plate was garlicky and tender to the taste. Over all with service, an outstanding experience. Also we were out side. It is a small elevated porch. Excellent view. Loved it. Also the bathroom is made for 5'11" guys. The mirror was 4inch x 4inch. And just my height. Sorry for the taller and shorter. I did not check out the ladies... oh wife just said it was terrible in the bathroom.
Awesome place. Great food. Friendly staff great sangria.
The duck fries and the new duck dish blew me away
Great tapas! Awesome place for a romantic dinner for two
(Translated by Google) Very good tapas in a Spanish atmosphere  (Original) Très bon tapas dans une ambiance espagnole

This restaurant is the one I like best. I go to a lot of restaurants but here I  constantly return again and again. The stuff is very chummy and the food they serve is so fresh and tasty. I would always prefer to have a decent meal here. I highly recommend this place.
Studio 54 tribute was spectacular! [Its a good restaurant, too ;)]
Best date night in Lafayette.
Excellent food atmosphere and service. Thank you
Awesome atmosphere!!!  Food is incredible,  drinks are amazing!!!
Classy, best cocktails in Lafayette.
Its Pamps.   good food, great ambiance.  Bartenders are top notch.  I spend way too much money here.....
This place is one of our favorites and where we have our 1st official dinner date.  My advice is get there early because this place gets pretty full.
Yummy finger foods! And finger foods are my fav.
Outstanding, traditional tapas in a beautiful setting. Top notch service. Definitely a destination if you're in Lafayette.
Great tapas. Paella was just ok. Josh is cute!  If I'm ever in Louisiana again, I'd certainly go back.
First time great. Last time: did not live up to our expectations.  Food was good, but not special or must go back. Drinks good.

The service, ambiance, and food provided is incredible. The prices are all fair and portions are generous, with a menu that is diverse and tight enough to fit a consistent feeling and still satisfy a picky eater.
This is a very unique restaurant with great food and wonderful atmosphere the wait staff was very knowledgeable of menu items and Eric made us feel right at home.
Fun friendly and great food!
Subtly fantastic food.  I wanted to eat all of the local food in Louisiana for the short time I was there,  but I'm glad I took a break from the gumbo at this place.
Great and friendly crowds gather here to enjoy good food. Food is served quickly and very tasty
Highly recommend! Very festive decor for Christmas. Great drinks! Server Steven was phenomenal!!
EXCELLENT Customer Service; Food Was Delicious🙌
Great atmosphere with top notch gourmet food.
The paella was fantastic! Recommended!

This place is pretty cool. The tapas I had were all good, but they are pricey and on the smaller side. So if you’re hungry be prepared to spend! (Money well spent of course.) The alcoholic beverages were good and moderately priced. The servers are great and knowledgeable about the menu.
Great flavors, great absinthe selections

Wow wow wow. Wasn't sure of what to expect having spent many a day in Spain sampling superb tapas. The food, setting and staff blew us away. We sampled the menu ... small plates, dishes, salads and more. We couldn't fit in desert but churros before we leave for the 🇬🇧 will be our goal.

Oh my God! I am almost embarrassed at myself for not having tried this restaurant being that it's in the same town I live in. Isn't sufficient to say the food was delicious. It was, in fact, completely mood-altering hunger satisfying, great atmosphere, and service that didn't come with a snobby smile. Everyone was very friendly and helpful and answered my questions regarding the foods that I couldn't even pronounce. A little pricey, but definitely worth it! You've got to try the ceviche!

Gorgeous atmosphere with exceptional service. As for the taste of the food, some bites were absolutely scrumptious (the bacon-wrapped dates, pork belly), but I found other bites to be just average (the garlic shrimp, the fois gras). We liked the restaurant overall, but we would probably not visit again.
Great tapas!

An absolute must dining experience. Food preparation and presentation score very high service was warm and prompt. They made us feel like we were VIPs. Definitely need to go again. Atmosphere was classic yet inviting. Quaint but a little luxurious. The chef knows what he's doing. Good wine selection. I positively liked it and would recommend it.
The paella was fantastic and were the lamb sliders.
Absolute amazing and delicious food. The best place I’ve been eating in USA so far! And the the service is so good and welcoming.
Great atmosphere, wonderful service and Awesome food!
Loved it! Loved the pork belly!
Overall, I would say, best upscale restaurant in Lafayette.
It can get a bit pricey, but the food is really good. Neat concept of many small plated meals.
Phenomenal tapas, small shareable plates, and great drinks
Great
Positively surprised by this place. Food and service were outstanding. Will be back next time I will be in Lafayette.
This place never disappoints. I've been going here since they opened. Again, it simply never disappoints.
Good food but salty & very little quantity serving.
Good eats. Great ambiance. Wine list could use some work.
Idk it's alright
Awesome takes on classic Spanish foods
Off the charts. Great flavors, cool environment. Highly recommend!
Great space, delish food & drinks, friendly service.  A real gem.  Highly recommend.

What a gem in the heart of downtown. The unique architecture and red door set it apart from the very beginning. Upon entering the restaurant it continues to stand apart from others in the area. The seating although close at first suddenly no longer matters.  The wine selection is diverse and the cocktails are creative. As a vegetarian I was able to find several delicious options: the arugula salad was lite and refreshing, the asparagus with poached egg was different and good, the flat bread with jalapeño was Smokey and scrumptious! If you’ve been wondering for years what’s behind that cute red door downtown it’s time to find out for yourself.
Amazing food, great ambiance
In Lafayette and little hungry?  Go to Pamplona tapas bar.  Pork belly crunchy outside juicy and tender inside.  Gouda  cheese and macaroni fantastic.  Duck fat French fries perfection.

Tapas service is not for everyone, but great as a change of pace. Our experience was very good. Perhaps best selection was the calamari. It was excellent. We have had calamari North, South, East, and West, and what we had here was best. The serving was large and fried to perfection. Perhaps most important was the abundant amount of tentacles, which are often absent.
Great place . Good people and good food
Amazing cocktails and tapas. Amazing
Loud but intimate. Date night friendly. The food Is excellent, light, and satisfying. The absinthe is a tasty change from tradition cocktails. The staff are friendly. Repeat customer.
Always good
Once you get past the host stand with the awkward hipster hostess, everything is great. The mussels and scallops were awesome. Bartender Alexa and Chef were personable and attentive.
We dined in there early, so everything wasn't quite ready yet, other than that pretty good place.
Nice drinks and food
Delicious White Sangria! Nice bar staff.
Excellent!
Beautiful and delicious

I recently dined at Pamplona with a friend and we had a superb lunch. The tapas menu is extensive and offers many local and Spanish style tapas plates. The daily lunch specials offer larger portions and are equally as tasty as the smaller tapas items. One of the best reasons to go to Pamplona is the cocktails - especially in the summer - the offerings of mixed drinks with crushed fruits and mint (like the fantastic Viceroy) are really delightful. As a local, I highly recommend this quaint downtown spot to locals and visitors alike.
Very good and tasty food
The best food i have ever had!!!!!!!!!!!!!

This is NOT an inexpensive restaurant! I went there once or twice per year when I lived in Lafayette. This time I was visiting from out-of-town with local friends. Really nice decor and ambience! I could be wrong, but the variety of dishes seems to have lessened; however, no doubt their respective quality, taste, and texture has not. Their freshly-made pitchers of Sangria still well complement the fare served.

Hands down, my favorite restaurant in Lafayette. Always an enjoyable dining experience. Great food, good drinks, professional servers. Ambiance is a bit loud, but fits with the theme. The duck fries are among the best French fries I have every tasted. Great tapas, highly recommend to anyone who listens

Here visiting and wanted something different. This was it. I loved the unique flavors and dishes. The small plates are great for sharing. We ordered several so we could have a tasting. I’d definitely go back.

We usually go for tapas and they never disappoint. This time we branched out and ordered the paella. It takes up to an hour to prepare so we had brussel sprouts - scrumptious-will-definitely-order-again delicious, and the tried and true duck fat fries. Then the paella ... we expected it to be equally wonderful, but, alas, it did not live up to expectations. A little soggy and bland. Too bad. In future we know to stick with the tapas.

Great! I am the first person to admit that I am not a huge fan of tapas, but this was different. I overlooked the higher price to food quantity ratio and went with the fact that the reviews were good and that my coworkers wanted to go to. Glad I did because it was very good. Service was great, seafood was great, just a very good meal. I highly recommend.
Wonderful food and service!

Lamb sliders were surprisingly tasty. Loved Brussels sprouts and albondigas. Patatas bravas are just deep fried shredded ones with a sauce. I'd have preferred "Patatas a lo pobre" instead. Service was excellent (thanks, Savannah!) and really nice ambience. We were there at lunch on a springtime Wednesday in 2019. Highly recommended.

What an amazing little tapas bar and so much more... The food is splendid, and the service is simply outstanding. Nice upscale dining. The escargot, when they have it, is definitely worth a shot. It is great.
Totally delicious! We left satisfied but not stuffed. So many different flavors, including things I would not normally have tried. Can't wait to go back!
Excellent restaurant for tapas. Very good food!
Hands down one of the best steaks in the state. Great selection of tapas. Love the carpaccio. Unique wine selection.

Definitely worth the 5-star rating. One of my favorite date places with my wife so far. We just ordered a few of the different plates offered and shared them. The food came quick and they spaced it well so that we only had one plate at a time on the table. Appropriate dress would be on the higher end of casual (snappy casual as I've heard it called) The food is very affordable for how fresh, unique, and tasty it is Our bill, with 4 different plates and a cocktail, was about $50.
Formerly owned by a Pamplona chef, lots of bull fighting and bull running pictures.
The cocktails here are consistently amazing, the food is inspired, and the service is very pleasant.
Awesome food, great staff
Love this place... but tonight the char broiled  oysters were very disappointing. No flavor.
Sweetbreads and the quail eggs are both must haves
amazing tapas
Fresh high quality food and service. Never had a bad dish.

The quail eggs are always good. The new items that I tried this time were the pork belly and escargot. Both were outstanding! We also had the bacon wrapped dates which were sweet but good. You could have those as dessert. However, that wasn't enough for me because I had the truffles too. Yum. If you can, go on Wednesday. They have great happy hour prices all day.
Hanger steak is the best. Escargot cooked to perfection. Duck fries oh my God, great and the wait staff and hostess , Cole , were wonderful and so friendly.
Excellent food, wine, and service.
Cold, crowded, seating not comfortable, not vegetarian/vegan friendly at any stretch of the imagination.  Will not recommend.
Nice atmosphere, good food, parking camb be challenging
Great food, great environment, and great service. Would recommend highly recommend highly to anyone looking for something new.
There are plenty of menu items to choose from, even things that a picky eater would enjoy if you brought them along. Can’t go wrong with the lamb sliders, though!
Beautiful restaurant, fantastic service and a well done tapas menu.
Great pizza. One of our stops during our restaurant hop in downtown Lafayette. Had a "straight outta central" and a pizza.
Excellent food. Mushrooms are a personal favorite
Great food, great service, great craft cocktails
Our very first stop in lafayette.  Really great beer and wine list.  We will absolutely be eating here next time.
Excellent food and drinks

The tapas and small plates each have an exquisite taste. My favorite are the bacon wrapped dates and the pork belly. What you see is the beet, fresh mozzarella, and mixed green salad. It comes with candied walnuts and I added scallops. The bartenders are masterfully skilled and drinks are always served perfectly.
One of our favorite restaurants in Lafayette. Service is always outstanding and the food and drinks are always on point. My favorite Sangria is found here.
Great service and quality tapas. Also loved the ambiance
Excellent food and service
Great food great nightly atmosphere. And when you go request Corey as your Waiter they don't come better than him.
Highly Recommend!
Awesome spot for date night!
Awesome as usual.  My family is from Spain and  Portugal.  The food and atmosphere reminds of my grandmother's house.
Authentic tapas with a great wine selection!
Wonderful service and delicious authentic Spanish Tapas. Very affordable too.
(Translated by Google) The restaurant is very nice and the food is super good  (Original) Le restaurant est très joli et les plats sont super bon

This place was AMAZING!!! I've never been to a restaurant like this before. I fell in love with the atmosphere and the food. Our server was superb. I suggest the seared tuna & the quail eggs and blood.
One of my husband and I's favorite places to go for a special occasion ♡

More of an old world, European style of dining experience and certainly enjoyable with impeccable service and exceptionally prepared offerings of food and beverages. While certainly not formal, still a pleasantly comfortable and fairly refined event with excellent dishes you would be hard pressed to find anywhere else within a large distance. A place where anyone who enjoys food or wine, and certainly if you appreciate both, should visit in an atmosphere that's conducive to enjoyment. You really shouldn't miss it.

What a treat! I would love to have a place like this at home! Every dish was cooked to perfection and seasoned superbly. Lamb was juicy, albondigas amazing, and wine / beer menu on point, with local craft on tap as well as a good selection of lesser known spanish wines. The quail eggs on morcilla were certainly a highlight!
Pretty much my favorite restaurant in this area. Everyththas always been excellent!
Bacon wrapped dates are to die for!
Best lunch in Lafayette!

(Translated by Google) Excellent service, very rich food. Do not forget to order the duck fries and of course the rich paella. The waiter are very attentive. The thing that made us happy was that they spoke Spanish, to feel more at home speaking our language. But it does not matter I speak English and can understand them  (Original) Excelente servicio, muy rica comida. No te olvides de ordenar las papas fritas de pato y por supuesto la rica paella. Los waiter son muy atentos. Lo u ocp que nos uniera gustado es que ellos hablaran español, para sentirnos más en casa hablando nuestra lengua. Pero no importa yo hablo el inglés y puede entenderlos
Amazing food and atmosphere
Had us on a waiting list for a hour when said 30 minutes. There were numerous empty tables. We left!  Thanks lame hostess.
The ceviche was bland and dry, but all other tapas we tried were good. Overall, still a positive experience.

The atmosphere is authentic and excellent, it truly feels like an upscale restaurant in spain. The service is cordial and fast, with even friendly recommendations. The food was the best part though, excellent flavour profiles and taste adventures!
Good food, good wine, and a very attentive staff.
Best local restaurant hands down!  Top of the line service & food! Highly recommend trying!
First tapas experience, it was fantastic.
Bloody good kai.
Super dope cocktails and fantastic bar staff.
Never disappoints. One of (if not the) best places in Lafayette. HIGHLY recommend.
There is always something interesting to try for lunch at our French table. Always, beautiful presentations. Great service, too!
The happy hours are amazing the bartenders are are very attentive
It’s a an ok place that thinks it’s trendier than it really is. Nothing crazy but if you’re in the area I guess check it out, but there are better spots. Unimpressed

One of the most unique and memorable dining experiences Lafayette has to offer. While the actual tapas motifs may take a back seat, the fantastic atmosphere, bold and delicious menu, and stellar selection of cocktails, liquors and wine, make this a must try when considering Lafayettes fine dining choices.
Food was really good. Staff was great. I will definitely visit again.
Impeccable staffing!! The food is amazing as well !
Awesome!
The paella and the red sangria are unforgettable! Theres still more to try though, I can't get enough of this place.
Best atmosphere,  awesome food, best service!!
Amazing food and service!
Wonderful food and service!
Good food
love it

By far the best Spanish restaurant in Louisiana! Excellent food quality, top notch service. Maintains elevated food consistency through busy festivale season. Great new host too; thank you for accommodating my large group. 👏😘❤️
The food was great. The staff could be a lot nicer. The people that go there were kinda trashy also. Not a great place to go if you want a quite meal.
Extremely fresh ingredients prepared in uniquely Spanish presentations; beet and goat cheese salad, scallops and calamari were all excellent!
Awesome
Nice and cozy, loved the atmosphere. If you want Paella you can order ahead. It takes 45 minutes to an hour to prepare. Need to go back to try more selections. Bacon wrapped lamb really good.
Daughter's Birthday celebration, food and service excellent
Staff went out of their way to get us a fantastic meal in time for curtain call! Real pros.
Wonderful cocktail bar, and the bread pudding was amazing

If you're looking to go somewhere with a great atmosphere with a large or small group this is it! Hell, you can even go alone. The tapas are great and it's nice to get several different ones and share. If you're looking for  an extensive cocktail menu to go with it, don't get your hopes up, but the ones they do have are great. I'd recommend for any occasion.

Pamplonas is a nice spot to have and excellent evening cocktail(IMO best in Lafayette) and appetizer or take a someone special and enjoy a fine meal. The atmosphere is suitable for either occasion. Not to be to opinionated my favorite
There is a French Table on Tuesdays at noon ;-)
Always amazing food and wait staff.
Nice cocktails

This was the first time my wife and I have eaten there and it was fantastic. The place is quaint inside and was nicely decorated. My wife and I tried the house salads, garlic shrimp, hanger steak and Apple bread pudding. I can not say anything bad about our entire experience. Everything was delicious and we will definitely be back when in Lafayette.
Nice place for tapas and reasonable prices BUT we had he paella which was a bit too heavy with rice and not a lot of meats. Sangria was a little too sweet.
Always great service and excellent menu!

A nice little high-end place with great tapas. The interior is dimly lit and romantic. They have a full bar with some interesting and unique cocktail options. The escargot was lovely. We also ordered the mushrooms, they came out very temperature hot but were delicious!
awesome meal
Great food and service
LOVE Pamplona. The oysters were amazing.
The food is always amazing.  We love trying new things every time along with out usual favorites.  The wait staff is attentive and helpful, despite the place staying packed.
Their food is so exquisite
Expect a wait... because it's just... that... good. Just enjoy the wait,  because you'll be happy you did.
Excellent dinner, service was great, thanks Emily! Duck Confit flatbread, Morcilla Quail Egg and Foie Gras are amazing!
Great food and service!!
Awesome food.  Incredible service.  Amazing wine list.
(Translated by Google) Beautiful cuisine and affordable price  (Original) Belle cuisine et prix abordable
Delicious and very trendy.
Great food and awesome drinks, it's expensive, but the great staff will take care of you, no matter how drunk you get, it's our favorite place to eat.
Incredible place great food. Pamplona's also has the best Gin and tonic in the state easily unless somewhere else is giving them away
(Translated by Google) very very good  (Original) muy...muy bueno
Awesome place

Great spot in downtown Lafayette. Perfect for sharing plates, sipping cocktails and watching the local scene. Plus, you never know who you might run into or what interesting conversations might take place. If you speak French, or are learning, you can join in on the French Table (Table Française) every Tuesday at noon.
Great food!
Great traditional food.

Ate here for my first time Saturday night, and can easily say it's my new favorite restaurant. Tried some very interesting new dishes, all of which were delicious, and the service and atmosphere were on point. Can't wait to go back!

Amazing food!.. great specials, fresh inovative fusion   cuisine that is great for sharing multiple small plates with friends... True Tapas. Oh yeah... The cocktails and wine selection are off the chain Tapas Notch.
A go to restaurant for my wife and I...never had a bad meal here. The cocktails are always top notch. Would recommend this restaurant to anyone who is adventurous when it comes to cusine.

Went for an early dinner and our waiter John-Henry was very attentive and considered our evening plans when we ordered. Even though he said they were expecting a dinner time rush, everything was relaxed and pleasant. Food came out at reasonable times. Wife loved the Duck Confit. We ordered the Filet and Ribeye and shared the tasty Duck Fat Fries! Even when the dinner rush came, service was excellent and meal was delicious.
Consistently wonderful! Lunch or dinner,you can satisfy your hunger and imagination!

Had the most amazing meal with a wonderful young lady behind the bar,(Drea) I think.  She was delightful and well informed my food was excellent as was the service! 7/19/17 I will definitely be back! NOLA
Great service from a knowledgeable staff, comfortable atmosphere, epic food and wine.
Great food, great service. Menu constantly evolving. The wine list is very good. Excellent atmosphere.
Finest eclectic dining experience in Lafayette.
Excellent food
Best cocktails and food in town
My favourite place in Lafayette to eat by far. There isnt a bad thing on the menu.
Great selection of tapas
These tapas are top. Top tapas.
The food is always awesome.

Love, love, love this place! The ONLY thing that could make it better is a lit fireplace because it feels like a Spanish home. The mushrooms, escargot, sliders, duck fat fries, flatbreads, and paella are all amazing. But the absolute best thing on the menu is the scallops. I mean, really. These things are a taste bud sensation! And their Happy Hour is one of the best in town. Under $4 for a glass of wine? Unbelievable! You can't go wrong here.
Amazing experience. Food, drinks, and service are outstanding.

We didn't have a very good experience there. We felt our food was bland and overpriced, and our service was really slow.  We couldn't hear each other because it was extremely loud. My girlfriend also got sick after eating the paella.  What really made the experience terrible was that we spoke to two managers about our experience. The first was extremely condescending and rude, and he only offered excuses and implications that we are at fault for having a poor experience. He argued with me the whole time instead of listening to me.  The second manager was more courteous and apologetic, but other than the attitude of the first manager, he also explained that there was nothing he could do about any of our concerns.  I walked out only somewhat dissatisfied with the experience, but after the treatment I received from management, I'm not going back.
“Amazing experience” We tried Rodizio in Lafayette, LA for the 1st time and we fell in love. The staff was great and the food was amazing. We can wait to go back again.
"My Husband and I love this place after we ate we walked along the river."
Great Spot!
Wonderful food, a great bartender, and exceptional service!  What more could you ask for?
Excellent, unique and wonderful atmosphere!
Had the roast beef, which is excellent. Sandwiches are big and packed; bread is excellent. Comfortable setting. A real Lafayette treat.
Great people, food, and drinks. Absolutely delicious. One of my favorite places to go.

This is one of the best, if not the best, restaurant in Lafayette.  We have never had a bad dish.  The wine is excellent --- if you have not tried Spanish wine (or if you have and liked it) this is the place to go.  Whatever you decide to eat (and the pork cheeks are wonderful) desert is the bacon wrapped dates.  This was our weekly date night restaurant before we moved.  When we come back to town this is where we go.  Put it at the top of your list.

My absolute favorite place in Lafayette for a appetizers and drinks or a great full meal. The staff knows the menu and options in-and-out, but the best thing is the drinks. Pamplona makes their own bitters, tonic water, and other "drink things" and take pride in the quality of their drinks.
Very pleasantly surprised to find this excellent spot in Lafayette!
Favorite place in Lafayette. The bartenders are nothing short of magical and the menu is adventurous and beautifully crafted.

A little bit expensive but the food was amazing. My boyfriend and I would always get the same items every time: duck fat fries, escargots, & hanger steak. Cocktail menu is yummy!! Order these because you won't regret it! Will always come back.
Awesome

Our waiter knew everything about every wine on the menu.  The pork cheeks are the best part of the pig. I didn't know that till last night.  Kind of expensive, but cheaper than some places.  Best bread pudding in Lafayette.
One of the best eating experiences I've had in Louisiana.

This is probably my favorite place in Lafayette. I love the food, I love the people here, I love the decor, the building, the street, the parking lot across the street and what not. This list could go on forever. I proposed to my wife here, so you can understand how special this place is to me. Coming down to food, the duck fat fries are to die for. I mean literally. I've had days when I went there just to have the DFF. We've probably had all of the drinks they concoct, and it just has a way very different from other bars. The chef's specials are amazing each time as well. We generally order off of the chef's special.  Overall, it's a place you must must must visit!  Cheers!
Very good selection of tapas. Was just driving through. Great service. I recommend their cervice, that sauce is heaven.
Great drinks, delicious food and good company. You just need to go!
One of the better restaurants in Lafayette. Best cocktails in the city, in my opinion. Atmosphere is great here and the service is always exceptional. I come here every time I'm in town.
Best crafted cocktails in Lafayette, LA Talented cooking leadership and staff provide an always impressive experience.
On the pricier side but the food was delicious. Try the quail eggs for sure.
Quail eggs, snails, sliced baguette fried with a bit of duck fat and flan. If I was not driving, I would have had a glass of Taylor's port as well :)
Wonderful place, food was excellent along with great service! A must visit when you are in town!

Amazing tapas, the best I've ever had. Depending on what you order, you can eat there for $20 or $60, but either way, you'll leave full and satisfied.  Our hostess was very patient when we missed our reservation by about ten minutes; we called beforehand and she had our table held just as was promised. The waitress that served us was very kind and enthusiastic, offering her advice when needed and working with us to create an order that would please us. Aesthetically, the place was romantically dim, and held a kind of theme that would remind one of Pamplona, Spain (hence the name). Overall I would give this restaurant a big five stars for their service, their atmosphere, and their deliciously fancy food.
Great food, great people!  A must for anyone in the Lafayette area!

I have dined at this restaurant several times since returning to Lafayette in early 2008.  It has never failed to please my palate.  One of my favorite tapas at this restaurant is the smoked gouda and mac!

I don’t often eat at Pamplona, the food isn't worth the price to me but the bar is amazing. The bartenders are the best downtown by far, no contest. Anson and James, two of their bartenders, might be the best in Lafayette. If you are looking for a more mature bar that generally tends to keep out the frat boy element this is your place. Sophistication and culture abound.
The food was amazing, the waitresses helped us order things off menu, and the drinks were the best I've ever had

PHENOMENAL!!! Went there after finding it on GoogleMaps. We were not dissappointed. The selection of wines, food were outstanding. The places was immaculate and the ambiance could not be beat! This place is a gem and did not dissappoint me (after eating there 3 times in one week while on business). The staff was friendly, knowledgable, attentive, cute and provided us with a great dining experience. You get what you pay for and this was worth every penny! Quality, fresh, tasty, innovative!!!
